item.title: Archive - The Gordon Parks Foundation
item.description:
Archive - The Gordon Parks Foundation

The Gordon Parks Foundation permanently preserves the work of Gordon Parks, makes it available to the public through exhibitions, books, and electronic media and supports artistic and educational activities that advance what Gordon described as "the common search for a better life and a better world."

item.title: 3 Myths About Bisexuality, Debunked by Science
item.description:
3 Myths About Bisexuality, Debunked by Science

Bisexuality is the tendency to be sexually attracted to both men and women. To some, this may sound like a superpower doubling one's romantic options (and odds). But in real life, bisexuality can be an awkward identity to have, creating a challenge truly fitting in with either the "straight" or LGBT communities.

item.title: QWOC Media Wire
item.description:
QWOC Media Wire

Queer Women of Color Media Wire is a media publishing and advocacy organization that amplifies the voices of Lesbian, Bisexual, Queer, Transgender women and gender non-conforming people of color, diaspora, and other racial and ethnic minorities around the world.
